      "description": "The dataset provides medical background data related to the pregnancies of participating mothers  (affection status: mothers who gave birth to a preterm [cases] or term [controls] infant): e.g. presence/absence of hypertension, diabetes, preeclampsia, number of previous pregnancies, type of delivery,  presence/absence of placenta abruptio or, amount of amniotic fluid present; in addition, data about mother's lifestyle (smoking, alcohol and other drug consumption) and general socio-demographic data (age, educational level, ethnicity) are provided. General data about the infants are also included, e.g. gestational age, birthweight, and gender.",
